The paper discusses the sensitivity of probabilistic queries to changes in network parameters, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of probabilistic models and the analysis of their robustness also suggest a connection to data science (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the mention of analytic results and bounds on the impact of parameter changes suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
